name: Miglė Skrebė
note:
Results: 
Company Name: Pigu.It
Company Website: http://pigu.lt
Contact Person: Miglė Skrebė
Product: Company offers nearly 140’000 consumer products, including household appliances, electronics, beauty & fashion, children goods, sports, DIY. Company is the only online retailer in the region to implement advanced warehouse management systems. Continued investment in the warehouse platform allows for highly efficient order processing and inventory management. 
Specialties: Copyrighters, Translators (Lithuanian, Polish languages), IT managers 
Country-Location: Vilnius, Lithuania
Target Audience: Finland, Lithuania
Immediate Requirement: Miglė is looking for someone with knowledge of local languages like Lithuanian, Polish and to make translate checking of our candidates.
Next Step: Send all information about our company and CVs of suitable candidates.
Next Contact Date: Keep in touch by email.

We interviewed 3 candidates:

Bohdana https://rh-s.com/marketer/copywriter/bohdana-c/ - lives in Poland at the moment, she studied to be an English translator in business. She also worked as an assistant manager. She translated into English and into Polish languages.

Vitalii https://rh-s.com/marketer/content-managers/vitalii-d/ - studied in Krakow and studied Polish. He also studied Spanish and English languages.

Olena https://rh-s.com/marketer/lead-generation-managers/olena-m/ worked as a school teacher, as freelance translator. She worked abroad in Poland and learned polish language there. She also worked as a translator from Polish to Russian and Ukrainian languages and vice versa. Olena also works with the content of our website and translate from Russian language to French.

Fresh Results: The customer liked 3 candidates – Bohdana, Vitalii and Olena. But she wants to conduct tests and check the level of knowledge of the Polish language. And then choose few candidates for the project.
Next step: To make test tasks and send to the customer.
